The paper deals with computer vision techniques for detecting sky pixels in outdoor imagery, which is a core topic in the computer vision field. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, specifically a convolutional neural network, to select the appropriate algorithm for a given image, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the importance of sky detection in urban climate research, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
